spirit:component.spirit:name: wideBRAM_axi_cdma_0_1
spirit:component.spirit:description: The AXI CDMA provides high-bandwidth direct memory access (DMA) between a memory mapped source address and a memory mapped destination address using the AXI4 protocol. An optional Scatter Gather (SG) feature can be used to offload control and sequencing tasks from the System CPU. Initialization, status, and control registers are accessed through an AXI4-Lite slave interface.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_AXI_LITE_IS_ASYNC
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select this checkbox when the clocks are different.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXI_DATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the width of the data bus.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_M_AXI_MAX_BURST_LEN
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the Max Burst Length for read and write operation.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_USE_DATAMOVER_LITE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This would deliver a small footprint of CDMA.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INCLUDE_DRE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Checking this will enable the user to address the memory with unaligned address. This would infer more logic.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INCLUDE_SF
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Enable CDMA Store and Forward Functionality

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_INCLUDE_SG
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enabling Scatter Gather improves the performance to a large extent by fetching and queuing more descriptors.
